The paper is about memetic algorithms, which are a type of optimization algorithm that combines global search with local search. This makes it likely that the paper would be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which is the most relevant sub-category for optimization algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of heuristics and parameter tuning, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of data structures and algorithms for optimization, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses software engineering aspects of implementing memetic algorithms, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
